{
  "texts": [
    "We therefore leave the question of micro-targeting, as well as other AI-polling-dependent technologies, and their ethical implications, to other research.",
    "Turning back to you, the newly registered voter and Amazon customer, and you, the user who has unwittingly given away their data to the AI pollster.",
    "We can say the following: your privacy need not be violated when it comes to the collection and storage of your personal data, providing that the AI pollster uses state-of-the-art technologies, such as differential privacy or generative AI.",
    "In addition, although you might legitimately worry about your privacy when it comes to targeted predictions, you should also weigh this risk against the democratic benefits of such a practice, which we shall present in the following sections.",
    "This \"cautiously optimistic\" stance we are suggesting for this voter is in line with normative considerations around AI regulation (Smith and Miller 2023), which dictate careful balancing of the interests of technology-relevant actors-i.e., technology users and tech-companies, amongst others-and the publicgood provided by the mass deployment of the AI."
  ]
}